SIMPLE: percolator
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Percolator
<hw>Per"co*la`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, filters.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧[Tissues] act as
<xex>percolators</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Henfrey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A type of coffee pot in which the heated water is
driven by its boiling action up above a porous canister of coffee held
above the level of the water in the pot, and then filters (percolates)
back through the coffee thus extracting its essence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Pharmacy)</fld> <def>An apparatus for producing an
extract from a drug by percolation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Percomorphi</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
